Juneteenth is a day of reflection and renewal. It is a pride-filled day taken to appreciate the African American experience and is inclusive of all races, ethnicities, and nationalities in allyship.
Join us as we reflect on our past and acknowledge the work we still have to do. @meditatewitheve and @wizdomisms lead us in an exercise focused on increasing our ability to listen with our full attention, bringing more mindfulness and kindness to our allyship.

In these past months, we’ve all experienced moments of  uncertainty; steps back, steps forward, fear, excitement, change … just to name a few.  But we can say one thing for certain: it has been a lot. ⁠
⁠
As we step into this world of uncharted territory, we ask you to join us as we stop, sit, and breathe.⁠
⁠
Tune in as we work through change together and focus on ways to approach stress, sleep and anxiety through mindfulness, compassion and self-care. ⁠
⁠
Find your own kind of normal. It all starts with a few deep breaths. ⬆️ #FindSomeHeadspace

node.text: Taking time to connect with nature can have positive effects on our cognitive, emotional, and spiritual well-being, lowering anxiety and stress levels and improving brain function and attention span. You don’t even have to get outside and camp for the full weekend — simply looking out a window or tending to houseplants can have benefits.

node.text: For some of us, back to school means a return of the weekly stressors. One thing parents and kids can do together to help start the week off right? Set an intention together. node.text: We’ve all had it: a vague sense of dread that creeps up on a delightfully unstructured Sunday afternoon. Headspace meditation teacher @dorakamau is here to help in our new podcast Sunday Scaries by Headspace, only on @spotify. Over the next 12 weeks, join Dora every Sunday, as she explores new ways to think about time, providing tips for navigating those weekends with ease and heading into each week more mindfully.
